posts.title: This "shadow government" Democrats want to run is a joke, but Trump must arrest them on day 1, and here's why...
posts.content:
18 U.S. Code § 2384 - Seditious conspiracy

The admission of guilt is in the name and more importantly, in the titles bestowed. By proclaiming themselves as positions like "Attorney General" in a shadow government, they are effectively inciting rebellion and conspiring to overthrow the government, just from those acts alone.

Words and titles matter. Shadow government still has government in the name. By taking on these titles, that is a usurping of official government positions. Imagine if China for example, created a shadow government president of the US, who then went and talked to people as such, promoting their policies. It would be no different, and just as much of a problem in the long run.

Will they get anywhere with this "shadow government"? Likely not, they're just sore losers desperately trying to grasp onto power. But it doesn't matter how softly they try to play this game, it's not benign by any means, it's meant to mirror official government positions and usurp the government from those positions. It doesn't matter if people don't believe they are official, it's still an impersonation, no different than if you weren't a cop but still drove around in a cop car and police uniform. It doesn't matter if you didn't actually harass anyone with a direct impersonation, or didn't even interact with anyone at all, you'd still be arrested.

Let's also keep in mind they've even created shadow government foreign policy positions, like UN ambassador. If you had the official UN ambassador coming up to say one thing, and then a shadow ambassador coming up and saying another, that isn't just sedition, that's a direct subversion and violation of the Logan Act, 18 U.S.C. § 953.

There's no point in playing these game and waiting to see where it will go, because the longer they are allowed to do it, the more emboldened they will get, until it starts to become an actual problem, which makes it a problem from the start. They probably even want to be shut down so they can make Trump out to be a tyrant, which is exactly why it's better to shut them down sooner rather than later when they've cemented themselves, otherwise by the time you realize something must be done about them, rebellion will already be over the horizon and then we get the 2018-2020 riots all over again from a small but loud group of people.

Trump needs to nip this in the bud, and he has every authority to do so. Don't play their games. Just deal with them. The aim of this shadow government is clearly intended to normalize sedition and conspiracy to overthrow the government, while also crying "tyrant!" if you try to stop them. But the game should simply be shut down at its inception. Let them cry tyrant, because that's better than normalizing sedition, which can only ever lead to setting the stage for actual tyrants coming to power by force. It is a coup, even if under a different hat.
